@node "INTRO" ""
@prev ""
                            INTRODUCTION
                            ------------
              This program was written for Xenolink BBS software to
 enable access to CD-Rom files via a door. It will allow users to view
 the contents of the CD and select as many files as the sysop has
 configured, and add them to a list that is read by @{"MegaRXDL" link "MRXDL" 0}
 for download in the normal system fashion.

 The main feature of this door is that it uses existing text files on
 most BBS ready CD-Rom disks as it's source for the listings on
 Xenolink.. This means no more hours configuring CDs' or having 300+k
 files for config files on your hard drives..

@endnode

@node "NEWFEAT" "New Features"

                            NEW FEATURES
                            ------------

NEW FEATURE 1:
               MegaCD now can also take requests for files that are
 contained in CD-Rom disks that are NOT LOADED at the time of their
 call.  When the CD containg requested files is loaded, a CLI Arexx
 utility (MegaReqMan) is either run by the sysop, or automatically
 in a Cron event. This util will locate the files requested and copy
 them from the CD to a buffer directory, and then allow the user to
 download them next time they log in..

NEW FEATURE 2:
               MegaCD now supports a Search function and limited
 wildcard searches using pre-created search indexes..

NEW FEATURE 3:
               MegaCD now has a Icon based CLI arexx utility, called
 MCDList that will create file listings of your configured CD's,
 either in IBM format (CR/LF pairs), Amiga text format and now in
 AmigaGuide © format..

NEW FEATURE 4:
               You can now configure to have any section/directory of
 your hard drives look as though they are CD's or you can have it
 display files from sections, not actually in the Xenolink filecat
 and have them queued for download as if they were part of your
 normal filecat..  I use this for all my CD-Rom Filelists, which then
 makes them appear in the same area as the CD files. All files
 transferred from within this door and via MegaRXDL, maintain system
 file/byte ratios..


@endnode

@node "EXTRAS" "Extra Utilities"
@prev ""

                          EXTRA UTILITIES
                          ---------------
 * MCDList   - A custom file list creator.  Now makes AmigaGuide
               lists.  (CLI ONLY)

 * MCDReqMan - The Offline request manager.  Can be run by the
               Sysop when a new CD is inserted, or via a Cron each
               night.  (CLI ONLY)

 * MegaCDOnline.rexx - Run from a dummy login menu or from any
                       configured menu to show the user what CD-Roms
                       are currently loaded..
                       (Xenolink Arexx door)

 * MegaReq.rexx - The Offline request program..  Called from within
                  MegaCD..  This can not be run from a menu, and it
                  must reside in the same directory as MegaCD.rexx.
                  (MegaCD Arexx door)

 * MegaReqCH.rexx - A small program that can be run at login or from
                    any menu for users to check if any of their
                    requests have been collected and buffered for them
                    to download..
                    (Xenolink Arexx door)

 * Search.rexx - The search routines for MegaCD.. This is not run from
                 Xenolink, MegaCD starts and runs it when required..
                 It must also reside in the same directory as MegaCD.
                 (MegaCD Arexx door)

 * MegaRXDL - The main download function used with all the
              downloading that is carried out by MegaCD and it's
              utilities.  This Program is ShareWare.  It will
              operate and download files (with delays and a limit
              to the number of files downloaded in a batch download)

              Please support development of MegaCD and register your
              copy if you intend using it..

@endnode

@node "INSTALL" "Installation"
@prev ""

                      INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS
                      -------------------------

           This release of MegaCD has a lot of major changes since
 MegaCD125 and I recommend you rename your existing Doors:MegaCD
 directory and your Doors:MegaRXDL directory to some other names
 before commencing the installation. (Do not delete them as some of
 your configs can be used/modified for this new version)


PLEASE READ THE NOTES IN THE TOP OF ALL THE AREXX PROGRAMS INCLUDED
IN THIS PACKAGE

           I have not got around to writing all the docs into this
 Guide file, and some of the newer utilities I have not written docs
 for except for what is commented in the top of their program..

 All programs will have to have their variables set up for your
 individual BBS, so please read any comments in them as you do this.

 This Door saves a file in T:  called MRXDL<nodenumber>.sfl So it is
 IMPORTANT to have the configured filename in @{"MegaRXDL" link "MRXDL" 0}
 as the above, using a tilde code for the node in use..

eg: XenolinkDoor "^20000^2^Doors:MegaRXDL/MegaRXDL ~20 T:MRXDL~14.sfl"

 The door recognises most of the different files.bbs I have found,
 if you have found any that are different, let me know, as it might
 not take much to make it compatable.

 I have written the setup into 10 Steps to make it as easy as possible.

                   @{"    SHOW ME THE STEPS    " link "STEPS" 0}


@endnode

@node "STEPS" "Installation Steps"
@prev ""

                             SETUP
                             -----

STEP 1:
         I assume since you are reading this doc file that you have
         unarced the MegaCD archive.. :)
         Copy the MegaCD directory and the MegaRXDL directory to your
         DOORS: assign

This is an overview of their basic contents:

@{" DOORS:MEGACD/           " link "MCD" 0}@{" DOORS/MEGACD/BUFFER/    " link "BUF" 0}@{" DOORS:MEGACD/CLIREXX/   " link "CLI" 0}
@{" DOORS:MEGACD/CONFIGS/   " link "CONF" 0}@{" DOORS:MEGACD/DOCS/      " link "DOC" 0}@{" DOORS:MEGACD/FILELISTS/ " link "FLIST" 0}
@{" DOORS:MEGACD/HDINDEXES/ " link "HDIND" 0}@{" DOORS:MEGACD/REQUESTS/  " link "REQS" 0}@{" DOORS:MEGACD/SEARCH/    " link "Search" 0}

@{" DOORS:MEGARXDL/        " link "MRXDL" 0}

STEP 2:
        Start up your text editor and edit the variables found near
        the top of each: MegaCD.rexx, MegaCDOnline.rexx, MegaReq.rexx,
        MegaReqCH.rexx, Search.rexx, and in the CLIRexx dir, MCDList
        and MCDReqMan.

STEP 3:
       If required, edit the Entry.txt file that is displayed to the
       user as he enters MegaCD.  If not required at all, simply
       rename the the file to .Entry.txt.

STEP 4:
       Make up a text file called MCD.header as per example to be used
       by MCDList as a header in all your filelists, and as an intro
       screen in the AmigaGuide lists..

STEP 5:
       @{"Edit the MegaCD/CD.cfg" link "CDCFG" 0} file to suit you number of CD's and their
       details..  NOTE: DO NOT LEAVE ANY EXTRA COMMENTS IN THIS FILE.
       The example supplied shows how to set up for virtual CD's as
       in the setup for Filelists, and how to setup for CD's with no
       files.bbs lists in each dir as in ClipArtHeaven example.

STEP 6:
       Enter the CONFIGS/ dir and @{"edit/create config files" link "CDROMCFG" 0} for your
       CD's as per examples supplied..

STEP 7:
       Add the following commands to whatever menu you want:

 MegaCD:

       CMD = "R"
           {
              REXX "^2^Doors:MegaCD/MegaCD.rexx ~14 ~138 ~10 ~11"
           }

 MegaRXDL:

       CMD = "D"
           {
    XenolinkDoor  "^20000^2^Doors:MegaRXDL/MegaRXDL ~20 T:MRXDL~14.sfl"
           }

 MegaReqCH:

       CMD = "C"
           {
            REXX "Doors:MegaCD/MegaREQCH.rexx ~14"
           }

 MegaCDOnline:

      CMD = ""
          {
           REXX "Doors:MegaCD/MegaCDonline.rexx ~14"
          }

 At this point I will mention I run both MegaCDOnline and MegaReqCH
 from the one fake menu as a user logs on, and they have no choice
 as to entering each program.. example:

PreMainMenu.src

  CMD = ""
      {
        REXX "Doors:MegaCD/MegaCDonline.rexx ~14"
        REXX "Doors:MegaCD/MegaREQCH.rexx ~14"
      }

STEP 8:
       Start up MCDlister and if you have configured right and a
 configured CD is loaded, it will be shown in the list of loaded CD's.

 Hit either A for Amiga list or I for IBM list and follow the prompts.
 It will create a filelist in MegaCD/ dir for you..
 As the list is created, you will be displayed the directories as they
 are scanned, and if an error occurrs in your configuration, or the
 text file (files.bbs) is not found, you will be notified..  The
 listing will continue on a new line in the window, so if left on it's
 own, you will know by the number of directories left displayed after
 MCDLister  has finished are actual errors, and should be checked out..

 If you selected A for Amiga list you will also be prompted if you
 want AmigaGuide lists..

STEP 9:

 Once the filelist has been fully compiled with no errors you may then
 create an Index file for the CD to enable the searches and OFFLINE
 requests for that CD..  Hit I to start the INDEX creation..

 NOTE: both the File list creation and the INDEX creation can be
 interupted by hitting <ctrl>C to break.

STEP 10:

 If all works as it should then relax and enjoy, and have a beer!

 If not, double check your configs, especially the paths defined,
 and if still not right, try running Snoopdos or similar to see
 where the failure occurred, (Mainly incorrect paths!)..

 As a last resort if the program fails, add TRACE ALL near the top
 of the Arexx program, then from the CLI use TCO to trace the 
 program through as it runs..  TCC from the CLI will close this
 trace window for those not fluent with Arexx..

 If still in trouble, post me a message for HELP!  :^))

@endnode

@node "MCD" "MegaCD Directory"
@prev ""

 DOORS:MEGACD/

 Entry.txt         A text file that is displayed as a user enters
                   MegaCD. Rename this file or delete if it is not
                   required. If not found, MegaCD will simply skip
                   past without problems..

 CD.Cfg            The main config file for all CDs' available.

 MCD.header        A text file that is placed in your filelists as
                   a header.  If not found a default header is used.
                   Try and keep it to about 74 characters wide to get
                   a nice display in AmigaGuide lists..

 MegaCD.Rexx       The main program. (The Brains of the operation)

 MegaCDOnline.rexx The program run from a false menu at login to
                   display online CD's to users as they log in.

 MegaReq.rexx      This is a part of MegaCD.rexx and is called
                   by MegaCd when a user wants to make a request for
                   a file that is on an OFFLINE CD disk.

 MegaReqCH.rexx    This program is normally run from a fake menu as
                   the user logs in, possibly straight after
                   MegaCDOnline.rexx. Alternativly it can also be
                   started from the file menu..  It checks to see
                   if the user has any buffered files from requests
                   waiting for download..

 Search.rexx       This is the search function of MegaCD.. It can only
                   be called by MegaCD, and has to remain in this dir.

@endnode

@node "BUF" "Buffer Directory"
@prev ""

 DOORS/MEGACD/BUFFER/           

                   This is the directory that OFFLINE file requests are
                   copied to when found, until the user downloads them,
                   and tries to make further requests..  The user is
                   limited to the number of requests he can have, and
                   to make further requests, he will have to delete old
                   or fulfilled requests.. When he deletes his old
                   requests, the files that were buffered will also be
                   deleted from the hard drive.

@endnode

@node "CLI" "CLI Directory"
@prev ""

 DOORS:MEGACD/CLIREXX/

 MCDList          This is the Filelist creator and the Search Index
                  creator..  It is CLI only and is NOT a Xenolink door..
                  It will prompt you to select if you want lists created
                  or if you want to make a search index for any online CD.
                  Search indexes ARE REQUIRED to enable both the search
                  and the OFFLINE request functions for a particular CD.

 MCDReqMan        The OFFLINE Request manager..  Run it using the icon
                  manually or from the CLI or a CRON.. It has one argument
                  NODISPLAY if you run it from a cron and want no output
                  to a window.


@endnode

@node "CONF" "Configs Directory"
@prev ""

 DOORS:MEGACD/CONFIGS/
                  The directory that contains each CDs' individual
                  configuration.. Usually named similar to the CDs' name
                  as defined in the main CD.cfg file.
                  Plus DUMMY Configs for Hard Drive areas..
                  A few examples are included.

@endnode

@node "DOC" "DOC Directory"
@prev ""

 DOORS:MEGACD/DOCS/
                  A Directory containing all the doc files.. Please read
                  carefully as I am not the worlds best doc writer..

@endnode

@node "FLIST" "FileLists Directory"
@prev ""

 DOORS:MEGACD/FILELISTS/
                  A directory I have created and included as an example,
                  it contains two directories, one for IBM filelists and
                  the other for Amiga related filelists.. Each has a
                  files.bbs I wrote in a text editor with the contents
                  of the directory and a description..

@endnode

@node "HDIND" "HDINDEXES Directory"
@prev ""

 DOORS:MEGACD/HDINDEXES/

                 This directory holds a directory for each CD that does not
                 contain its' own index files in each dir.. Inside the dir
                 for the CD, there exists a complete clone of the directory
                 structure of the CD that did not contain any index files..
                 In each of these directories on the hard drive, you create
                 your own files.bbs text file containing the names and
                 description of each file found in the same dir of the CD..
                 REMEMBER to specify the path to this area in the .cfg
                 file for this CD.

                 An easy way to explain this feature is that MegaCD will
                 look to this area for the files.bbs list to display to
                 the user, and if a file is selected for download, MegaCD
                 will use this dummy path to the file.bbs, the file named
                 in the files.bbs that the user selected and the CDName:
                 found in the .cfg for that CD as the full path to the 
                 actual file to download...  Simple eh! I'm even confused,
                 but it works fine.. Check the examples for ClipArtHeaven.

                 A quick way to make these files.bbs for a CD with no
                 file descriptions is by using the DOS command LIST with
                 LFORMAT to give you the format, then redirect it to a
                 file..

@endnode

@node "REQS" "REQUESTS Directory"
@prev ""

 DOORS:MEGACD/REQUESTS/
                 This directory is where the user's requests (<name>.req)
                 are found, the CD's request file (<cdname>.req) and the
                 user's Found & Buffered files list (<name>.fnd) are all
                 located..
                 If a file with the name of a CD disk .req is found in
                 this directory then someone has got requests for files
                 found on that CD pending..  You may like to insert the
                 CD and run MCDReqMan to fulfill the requests or leave
                 it to automatically fill the requests next time the CD
                 is loaded when your cron event runs MCDReqMan.

@endnode

@node "Search" ""
@prev ""

 DOORS:MEGACD/SEARCH/
                 This directory contains the search index files for any
                 CD disk you wish the search or OFFLINE request features
                 to work with..
                 After configuring a CD, use MCDList and create a filelist
                 then run Index on the same CD, and a search index will be
                 created in this dir for the particular CD..


@endnode

@node "FEATURE" "MegaCD Features"
@prev ""

                       FEATURES
                       --------
 * Uses Files.bbs/00_Index/INDEX files and others that exist on most
   CD-Rom disks, completly avoiding extra Hard Drive wear&tear as
   all the files and descriptions are read directly from the CD..

 * Ability to take File Requests that exist on OFFLINE CD-Roms and
   process the request lists when the CD is available.. The requested
   files are then Buffered to the hard drive and the user who made the
   request is then able to download his files during a future call..

 * Very fast file searching from Arexx..

 * ALL filemarking, directory changes etc are done by number.  No
   need to mark files by their full name..

 * Has it's own filelist creator that will create custom lists in
   either IBM (CR/LF), Amiga text or AmigaGuide© formats!!

 * Normal system downloading _WITHOUT_ attaching to messages.!!

 * Ability to configure CD-Roms _WITHOUT_ file lists in each directory 

 * Ability to access virtual devices on hard drives that appear as
   mounted CD-Roms..  I use a virtual as an area for CD-Rom filelists
   so the filelists for all CDs' are found within the door..

 * Marked file listing including estimated D/L time and total bytes marked.

 * File ratios supported from within the Door.

@endnode

