@node "HISTORY" "History and Changes"
@prev ""


 MegaCD DOOR program and associated Utils
            © 1994-1995 David Huckett..
 Xenolink  CD-Rom Door.



History docs written as I change different things..

 WARNING MegaCD.rexx
 -------------------

   CD-ROMs that have no name and show up on Workbench as Unnamed must
 only be used one at a time.. You can not have three volumes loaded
 in drives all called Unnamed.. It will confuse the door.

   I use a NEC CDR25 Rom Player that is renown for its' ability to
 cause trouble, and have found that when the STATEF Arexx command is
 used on some files to get the bytesize, or using any Dos command to
 access the drive to get info about a single file, that some sort of
 endless loop starts and causes the CD-Rom door to go blank.. The
 only way out is a reboot..

NOTE:3-Jul-95 I think I may have fixed this BUG as I changed a few
 routines about and it hasn't appeared for a few weeks..

   The only command that causes this is when I look for the byte size
 of a file, so if you encounter this problem, all you need to do is
 turn OFF the display of the bytesize when marking or listing marked
 files by changing the Global variable called BYTECHECK either 'Y' to
 display file bytesize or 'N' to disable it..


 MegaREQCH.rexx Vers 1.0
 -----------------------
 25-Sep-95    Made this small util to run from a fake menu as the user
              logs on, or from a command in any menu to allow a user
              to see if any of his requests have been filled and his
              files are waiting for download..
              I use it in a fake menu at login, and they are asked if
              they wish to add their requests to the list for MegaRXDL
              to download..



 MegaREQ.rexx Vers 1.01
 ----------------------
 23-Sep-95    Had an idea to allow a user to request files
              that he found in the CD-Rom file lists created
              by MegaCD door, when the CD was not available
              at the time he logged on.. This would be a two
              part program.. One to recieve the request from
              the user, and the second to be run say in the
              midnight script, that would check the requested
              files against the loaded CD-Rom(s) at the time
              and if found, transfer the file(s) to a Hard
              drive directory and Next time the user logs on
              he can download the requested files from the hard
              drive.


 MegaCD.rexx Vers 1.27
 ---------------------
 22-Sep-95   Search function working OK now, so I will release for
             users to test out..
             OFFLINE Requests now implemented and working.. Use the
             function and send reports in to me on any ideas on the
             function...
             This is a grey area as far as I have not seen it in use
             on any other system, but so far here it works fine..

 MCDReqMan Vers 1.02
 -------------------
 16-Sep-95   Complete rewrite of all the OFFLINE request functions.
             Everything was too slow and was to many separate things
             for a user to remember...
             Been away with work and thought up new ideas..
             Good to be back home.

 12-Aug-95   First attempt at filling file requests from users, works OK
             but not easy to set up.  Way too slow as it has to check
             for each file requested on all loaded CD's.. Have to work
             on a better idea..!


 Search.rexx Vers 1.01
 ---------------------------
 12-Sep-95   Search function working well enough to put online for
             users to try out..  Had to make numerous changes, then
             decided it was time for a rewrite.. This is the best and
             fastest way I could think of doing searches of ~3000 files
             using Arexx..



 MCDList Vers 1.02
 ---------------------------
 12-Aug-95   Made it also have the option to create the list in
             AmigaGuide© format..

 8-Jul-95    Added function to create a file in a NEW directory called
             SEARCH inside the MegaCD dir.. The file created is then
             used for the file search function within MegaCD.. When I
             write it :)  IMPORTANT.. If you add a new CD or change
             the configs for a CD then you must rerun this util and
             create a new search index file.
             The sysop can try out the search function from within this
             program to see how fast it actually is from AREXX....

             I have made a replacement table of Tokens for most file
             extensions to make the size of the search file as small as
             I possibly could.. This replacement table saves around
             10,000 bytes on an average CD-Rom' search index..


 MegaCD.rexx Vers 1.27
 ---------------------
 14-Aug-95   added option AllowWithNoCredit for users with no
             credit to be able to have a look around..
             Suggested by Peter Chalmers..
             Added a new file called entry.txt, if found by MegaCD
             during startup, it will display the file to the user..

 12-Aug-95   Removed MegaCDLister.rexx function from within door
             and made it into a CLI program..  It is now called
             ListerCLI.rexx..

 31-July-95  Added bit to allow just to show online CDs only..

 3-Jul-95    Set up so filelists could be created from within door if
             the access level was 255..

 MegaCDLister.rexx Vers 1.02
 ---------------------------
 3-Jul-95    Added the ability to have a text file included in the
             filelist as a header type banner..
             Complete rewrite to enable filelists to be written in
             Amiga text format or IBM format (CR/LF pairs on each
             line)..
             Changed routines a bit so it could be called from within
             MegaRXDL..
             Initial release date for this util..

 MegaCDLister.rexx Vers 1.01
 ---------------------------
 20-Jun-95   Finished first fully working version to create filelists
             from the configs in MegaCD.. (Actually started it today)

 MegaCDOnline.rexx Vers 1.01
 ---------------------------
 14-Jun-95   Changed initial release around a bit to have the option of
             either displaying all the CDs' that were configured and the
             loaded ones highlighted, or simply display only loaded CDs'.

 MegaCD.rexx Vers 1.26
 ---------------------
 7-Jun-95    Added code for if user did not leave correctly and the temp
             file remained..

 MegaCD.rexx Vers 1.25
 ---------------------
 3-Jun-95    Made Time limit just under that of system time to get users
             out of door before timelimit exceeded.
             Set to get the time from Xeno ~ codes as well as baud rate..
             Tidied up screen displays
             Made possible for two nodes to use at once.. Possibly more..
             Allowed switch for a bug with some slower CD-Rom drives when
             finding byte size of some files in deep directories.
             Estimated time to download all marked files now working..

 MegaCD.rexx Vers 1.24
 ---------------------
 14-May-95   Started routines to work out Baud rate and CPS and average
             esimated Download time.
             Also started making multi node capable.

 Search.rexx Vers 1.00
 ---------------------------
 13-May-95   Started with an idea to create a search util for files
             on the CD..  Working version, but takes between 1 and 3
             minutes to search through 8-10 thousand files on a CD
             using a stock A500 and a single spin CD drive..
             I consider it a bit slow, so put on hold until I work
             out how to do binary searches in C as well as create
             Token Index files.

 MegaCD.rexx Vers 1.23
 ---------------------
  10-May-95  Changed the directory display from MSG to allow for
             systems using differing width character fonts and any
             changes to colours or display widths.
             Changed the file display section a bit to stop runover
             into the next line..
             Also added a delay if index file not found, so user is
             told and notifies the sysop.

 MegaOCDFR.rexx Vers 1.00
 ------------------------
 8-May-95    Had an idea to allow a user to request files that he
             found in the CD-Rom file lists created by MegaCD door,
             when the CD was not available at the time he logged on..
             This would be a two part program.. One to recieve the
             request from the user, and the second to be run say in
             the midnight script, that would check the requested
             files against the loaded CD-Rom(s) at the time and if
             found, transfer the file(s) to a Hard drive directory and
             post a message with the requested files attached..
             Part 1 completly finished and working.. Now some spare
             time to get around to finish part 2 for the Cron, that
             will copy and attach the requested files if found..

 MegaCD.rexx Vers 1.22
 ---------------------
  7-May-95   Added basic file/byte ratio support and User status
             display on main screen.   
             Added Maximum marked files option.
             Allowed for users with 0 uploads & 0 downloads.


@endnode

@node "CDCFG" "CD.Cfg file Configuration Setup"
@prev ""
  Setup for MegaCD Door © David Huckett

#   CD.cfg setup..  ** IMPORTANT  PLEASE READ **

  *** New Additions At bottom for Hard Drive area downloading..

 The format of this file is important, if done incorrectly your
 screens will be a mess..  Follow the example and you will get the
 idea..

 Line 1:   This is the total number of CD entries you have in this
 file.  The door will only read that many entries..  If you add
 another CD and its' entry to the bottom of this list and it does
 not show up when you enter the door, you most likely forgot to
 increase this number by one..

 Line 2:   Is the beginning of the individual CD configs.. 6 lines
 make up a full config for each CD..  So This is the FIRST line of
 CD Config.  It is the PATH NAME of the CD including the : If you
 use CD0: for example it will not work properly, especially if you
 have multiple CD DRIVES.

 Line 3:   Is the TITLE you wish to call the CD and is what is
 displayed to the users as they enter the door.. Keep it SHORT, so
 it doesn't stuff up your display.. I allowed 15 Characters for this
 field.

 Line 4:  This is the FULL path including the name of your config
 file for the CD named in line 2..

 Line 5:   This is the description of the CD named in line 2.. Keep
 it about 40 characters to have the display remain tidy..  It is
 what is displayed to the user as they enter the door.

 Line 6:   This is the line entry for what levels you want to access
 the particular CD.. It must have an entry, so I use 1, which is not
 used as a access level number in my template.config.  Using:
 0 10 20 30 55 as an entry on this line will prevent users on those
 levels being able to get any further and accessing the loaded CD..
 **BUT** they **WILL** be able to see the name of the CD and its'
 description, so be wary of Adult CD's etc.

 Line 7:   This is the next step on line 6.. If you enter an access
 level number here, the users on this level **WILL** **NOT** be able
 to even view the name or the description of the CD. **BUT** remember
 the same level number must be in the previous line to prevent them
 from entering the CD listings and downloading.  REMEMBER Both these
 last two lines must have a number entered, so use a level you don't
 use on your system if you allow everyone to view and access a
 particular CD.

 The rest of the file is a repeat of lines 2 to 7 for each CD you
 wish to configure, and remember to have line 1 display the number
 of CDs.

 EXAMPLE:

 -------------8<----------
 4
 DOORS:MegaCD/FILELISTS/
 CD-Rom Filelists
 Doors:MegaCD/Configs/Filelists.cfg
 Filelists for all online CD-Roms
 1
 1
 AMINET_0294:
 Aminet 2
 Doors:MCDD/Configs/Aminet2.cfg
 February 94 Aminet CD(Amiga)
 1
 1
 AMINET_0794:
 Aminet 3
 Doors:MCDD/Configs/Aminet3.cfg
 July 94 Aminet CD (Amiga)
 1
 1
 AMINET4:
 Aminet 4
 Doors:MCDD/Configs/Aminet4.cfg
 November 94 Aminet CD (Amiga)
 1
 1

@endnode

@node "CDROMCFG" "Individual CD-Rom Configs"
Example CD-Rom config file for MegaCD © David Huckett 1995

THESE CONFIG FILES RESIDE IN THE CONFIGS DIRECTORY..

  You will require one of these config files for each CD you configure
 to use in MegaCD Door.

 The format is simple and is as follows:

 LINE 1: Is the CD name or path LIKE AMINET4:  This must always be
        the device name with a : *AVOID* using CD0: as it won't work
        in all cases, especially in multinode systems or when swapping
        Disks.

 LINE 2: This is the first part of the path to where the index files
        are found if you do not have any text index files in the
        directories of the CD-Rom.  This entry, when the paths
        defined in lines 5 onwards are appended is the FULL path to
        the index/files.bbs text files..
        You specify a path on your hard drive where it can find the
        index or files.bbs text files you made up yorself.. Please
        check out the example configs for filelists and the
        ClipartHeaven CD.

        NOTE:   When configuring to use CDs' that have no index files
        in each	directory, or configuring to use directories on a
        Hard drive as a virtual device within this door, you must
        recreate the same directory structure as the CD-Rom you wish
        to access, on your hard drive.. Each of these cloned
        directories should then contain	only the files.bbs text file..
        An example is included with the	Clipart Heaven CD as well as
        an example of how to set up a virtual area.. (FileLists
        directory and filelists.cfg)

LINE 3: Is the text file found in the directory of files you make
        available for download.. Eg. Files.BBS, INDEX, or 00_index.txt

LINE 4: Is the trick one.. It is the number of lines at the top of most
        files.bbs or 00_Index.txt files that are just titles and shit.
        MegaCDDoor will not display the number of lines defined here.
        When you enter the door and display a directory, you should see
        the first file as 1.Filename.lha  description, not 1.and a
        heap of text.

All the rest of the lines in this config file are in the order of:

FIRSTWORD                 RESTOFLINE with spaces between ..

The first word is the FULL PATH EXCLUDING the line 2 entry to the
 named directory (Path to the Files.bbs file)

Example:

Aminet3:aminet/biz/demo/files.bbs
  ^^   |      ^^^      |   ^^^ LINE 2     Firstword     LINE 3

The rest of line is the description of the directory contents that is
 displayed to the user so he can select the file area to enter...

You can have unlimited paths and descriptions here.

 eg:
 ------------8<---------
 AMINET4:
 AMINET4:
 Files.BBS
 0
 aminet/biz/dbase/  Data base software
 aminet/biz/demo/   Demo commercial
 aminet/biz/misc/   Misc business
 aminet/biz/patch/  Commercial patches
 aminet/comm/bbs/   BBS programs

 etc. etc.
 ----------------8<---------

 UNNAMED:
 DOORS:MEGACD/HDINDEXES/CLIPARTH/
 Files.bbs
 0
 Advertse/       Advertising clips in PCX format
 Advertse/tif/   Advertising clips in TIF format
 Aircraft/       Aircraft clips in PCX format
 Aircraft/tif/   Aircraft clips in TIF format
 Animals1/       Animal clips in PCX format
 Animals1/tif/   Animal clips in TIF format
 Animals1/cats/  Cat clips in assorted formats
 Animals1/dogs/  Dog clips in assorted formats

----------------8<------------
 DOORS:
 DOORS:
 Files.bbs
 0
 MegaCD/FILELISTS/IBM/   IBM CD-Rom file lists.
 MegaCD/FILELISTS/AMIGA/ Amiga CD-Rom file lists.


Any problems contact me in any of the Xenolink support echoes.

Cheers, David Huckett  
@endnode

@node "MRXDL" "MegaRXDL Shareware Download program"

                        MegaRXDL by D. Huckett ©1995

 Introduction

 MegaRXDL is a Shareware Download Interface Program for Xenolink BBS.
 It allows users to download files from Xenolink as normal downloads
 or if a text file defined in the command line exists, it will add
 the contained filepaths and files to the users download list, and
 continue with a normal system download..

 This makes it a very handy util for external programs written in
 Arexx, which are unable to carry out direct downloading without
 attaching to messages via Junkmail ©.. It is part of my Shareware
 CD-Rom door program for Xenolink, but released also as a separate
 door for those who want to interface it with existing programs that
 are unable to do direct downloading..

 NOTE: Upon registering MegaRXDL you will obtain a keyfile that will
 enable the full functions of this program, to use as you wish on
 your system.

 You may also register this program on it's own to use with other
 software..

@endnode

